<p>
  Find the dimensions
  <m>l \times w</m>
  of a rectangle with area
  <m>$a \text{yds}^2.</m>
  whose perimeter is as small as possible.
</p>

<p>
  Answer (in sq. yds.):
  <m>l=</m>
  <answer>
    <award>
      $ans1
    </award>
  </answer>
  and
  <m>w=</m>
  <answer>
    <award>
      $ans2
    </award>
  </answer>
</p>

<solution>
  The answer is a square, so each side length is <m>$ans1</m>.
</solution>
